us Historicus 7.35; σφέας [prev. author] 9.77; τινὰ θανάτῳ [prev. author] 3.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τινὰ φυγῇ, πληγαῖς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.65, 8.74 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ζημιοῦσθαι ζημίαις ἐσχάταις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 31.26; θανάτῳ 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.9, “PTeb.” 5.92 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θανάτῳ καὶ πᾶσι τοῖς ἐσχάτοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 297e; χρήμασιν καὶ ἀτιμία [prev. author] “Lg.” 721b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2210","accentedUnicode":"ζημιόω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2209","matchingForm":"ζημία","stepTransliteration":"zēmia","gloss":"damage/loss","_zh_tw_Gloss":"破壞, 有損","_es_Gloss":"daño/pérdida","_zh_Gloss":"破坏, 有损"}],"shortDef":"to lose","mediumDef":"to lose <br />(pass.) to forfeit, suffer loss or damage","stepGloss":"to lose","stepTransliteration":"zēmioō","count":6,"_es_Definition":"(solo con voz pasiva) perder, sufrir una pérdida ; ser castigado (1CO.3:15)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 遭受損失,損害, 受傷<br>2) 受懲治 (林前 3:15)","_zh_Definition":"1) 遭受损失,损害, 受伤<br>2) 受惩治 (林前 3:15)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"thiệt hại; mất mát","_zh_tw_Gloss":"賠上","_es_Gloss":"perder","_zh_Gloss":"赔上"}]}